  <section>
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>
          How to build
      </h1>
    </div>
    <h2>
        Requirements
    </h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/devkitpro/" target="_blank">devkitPro r18 (buildscripts 20060412)</a>
          (You need to use version r18. Do not use the latest release!)
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h2>
        Steps
    </h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
          Execute the following commands in Terminal.
        <pre>
$ tar ztf bulletgba-5.0.tar.gz
$ cd bulletgba-5.0/bulletgba/
$ make
</pre>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>
          How to replace graphic resources
      </h1>
    </div>
    <h2>
        Steps
    </h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
          Download <a href="files/tools.tar.gz">tools.tar.gz</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
          Execute following commands to setup gba-tools.
        <pre>
$ mkdir ~/gba
$ cd ~/gba
$ tar zxf tools.tar.gz
$ cd tools/bmp2c
$ make clean all
</pre>
      </li>
      <li>
          Modify graphic resources under bulletgba/images.
      </li>
      <li>
          Execute following commands to convert graphic resources.
        <pre>
$ cd bulletgba-5.0/bulletgba/images/
$ ./conv.sh
</pre>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>
          How to add BulletML
      </h1>
    </div>
    <h2>
        Requirements
    </h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
          You need PHP 5.0+ to convert BulletML to C++.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h2>
        Steps
    </h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
          Extract source code.
      </li>
      <li>
          Put BulletML to bulletgba-5.0/bulletgba/generator/data/xml/user/.
      </li>
      <li>
          Execute following commands to convert BulletML into C++.
        <pre>
$ tar ztf bulletgba-5.0.tar.gz
$ cd bulletgba-5.0/bulletgba/generator/
$ make copy all
</pre>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>
          Supported BulletML
      </h1>
    </div>
    <p>
        The most BulletML are supported. But there are little exception.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>&lt;accel&gt; does not work properly.</li>
      <li>
          &lt;*Ref&gt; which contains $rand in &lt;param&gt; does not work properly.
<pre class="prettyprint lang-xml">&lt;fireRef&gt;
  &lt;param&gt;1.0 * 3.4 + 4.2&lt;/param&gt;     &lt;!-- *** This line works fine. *** --&gt;
  &lt;param&gt;$rand + 1&lt;/param&gt;           &lt;!-- *** This line does not work properly. *** --&gt;
&lt;/fireRef&gt;</pre>    </ul>
  </section>

